==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Laniary
<hw>La"ni*a*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>laniarius</ets>, fr. <ets>lanius</ets> butcher, <ets>laniare</ets>
to tear in pieces: cf. F. <ets>laniaire</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>Lacerating or tearing; <as>as, the <ex>laniary</ex> canine
teeth</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Laniary</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Laniary
<hw>La"ni*a*ry</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <er>Laniary</er>,
<pos>a.</pos>]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The shambles; a place of slaughter.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>A laniary, or canine,
tooth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Laniate</ent>⟦br⟧
